laboratory_examinations.findings: Increase in size of pancreatic cysts: Neck cyst 24 x 30 mm (previously 17 x 25 mm); Tail cyst 25 x 27 mm (previously 16 x 14 mm). Non-enhancing filling defects in the dilated main pancreatic duct. No enhancing lesions within cysts.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Notable interval increase in the size of pancreatic cysts compared to prior study.
